section.t:
In addition to its 6rd responsibilities, the 6rd CE is responsible for:
mapping between the IPv6 address pair presented by the IPv6 Host and IPv4 address pair designating the same multicast stream in the provider's IPv4 network;
translation from MLD presented by the IPv6 Host to IGMP forwarded toward the provider's IPv4 network;
using the reverse mapping from IPv6 to IPv4 address pairs to translate incoming IPv4 multicast streams to IPv6 before forwarding them to the IPv6 Host. Alternatively, decapsulating IPv6 multicast data packets from incoming IPv4 packets.

The Border Relay has the usual 6rd responsibilities. In addition, it is responsible for:
mapping between IPv4 address pairs received in PIM messages from the IPv4 network and IPv6 address pairs denoting the same multicast streams in the neighbouring IPv6 network;
interworking PIM between the IPv4 and IPv6 networks;
using the reverse mapping from IPv6 to IPv4 address pairs to translate and forward multicast data packets coming from the IPv6 network. Alternatively, using the reverse mapping to generate encapsulating IPv4 headers for the IPv6 packets before forwarding them as multicast IPv4 data.

